Length up to 2.0 mm, specimen examined (female) 1.3 mm. Colour in alcohol white (red when alive; 
Christiansen and Bellinger 1980
). Body shape cylindrical, abdomen slightly broadened in the region of Abd. III and IV (Fig. 1). Granulation homogenous.

PAO with one five-lobed vesicle (5 or 6 lobed; 
Christiansen and Bellinger 1980
), located in a depression with schitinised edges, subequal in length to the nearest pseudocellus (Fig. 5). Seta d0 on the head absent. Labral formula of setae: 4/342. Maxillary palp simple with two sublobal hairs. Labial type 0. Labium with four basal and five basolateral setae.
